frameDefinitions: The  Speaker expresses through language his wish to get the Addressee to act in some way that will help to bring about events or states described in the Content.
An Agent, by virtue of strength or forcefulness, controls, rules, or strongly influences some Patient in some Situation.
A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
An Agent behaves as if they were a particular individual or type of Simulated_entity with the intent of misleading observers of their behavior.
An Agent is described as pursuing an Activity, expending some effort.
A Location is characterized by a high amount of (often goal-oriented)
frameExamples: Mr Smithers always <t>encourages</t> the employees to stay late and work harder.
The fireballing righthander looked poised to <t>dominate</t> the Yankees yet again, striking out seven straight batters during one stretch
The belfast bank robbers <t>posed</t> as police.
Sky, a Korean War veteran, was <t>active</t> in his opposition to Vietnam and continues to protest current combat in Iraq.

This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the  <fen>Activity</fen> is pursued.
